==Scots==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[dol]]'', ''[[doel]]'' (modern ''[[deuill]]'') ‘mourning’, from Vulgar Latin ''[[dolus]]'', from Latin ''[[dolere]]'' ‘grieve’.  Later influenced by or reborrowed from early Middle English ''[[dool]]''.  Cognate with English ''[[dole]]''.

